  "about": {
    "bannerTitle": "Growing with people, technology, and trust.",
    "sectionCeoCaption": "CEO GREETING",
    "sectionCeoTitle": "CEO Message",
    "altCeoVideo": "CEO message",
    "ceoParagraphs": [
      "Hello. I am Kim Jung-ho, CEO of TNQ.",
      "TNQ started in 2012 as the mold division of TNP and became independent under the name TNQ in 2022 through a spin-off. We are a specialist in automotive body hot and cold stamping dies. We have grown with our customers based on our accumulated experience and technological capabilities.",
      "Since our founding, we have strived to build differentiated competitiveness through continuous investment and technology, and we have responded to our customers' trust with integrity and responsibility. We believe that TNQ's steady growth amid a rapidly changing industry is thanks to your support and trust.",
      "The automotive industry is undergoing major changes with new paradigms such as electric vehicles and autonomous driving. TNQ is preparing for the future of mobility by developing hot stamping dies for body lightweighting and cold stamping dies for high-strength steel.",
      "Going forward, TNQ will go beyond being a die manufacturer to become a trusted technology partner that creates value with customers, and we will achieve customer satisfaction through the highest quality and delivery competitiveness.",
      "We will grow into a trusted company in automotive body dies through constant R&D and innovation, and we will continue to build the future together with our customers.",
      "Thank you.",
      "Kim Jung-ho, CEO of TNQ Corporation",
      ""
    ],
